result.execSummary:
Travian Isaac White was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Travian Isaac White was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 8:40 AM Defendant Travian Isaac White not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Brian Van Schyndel in court for the State of Wisconsin. Digital Court Reporter: Hannah Wronkowski.  Defendant has been extradited.  BTC: Case dismissed.

10:20 AM Defendant Travian Isaac White in court.  Attorney Brian Van Schyndel in court for Travian Isaac White. Atty Erin Preston appears for the defendant. Digital Court Reporter: Hannah Wronkowski.  The defendant requests a Govenor's Warrant.  Defense requests bond be set.  Parties make bond argument.  State requests $5000 cash.  Defense asks for a $1000 cash.  BTC:  Court will not set bond, Defendant to be held without bond pending the Governor's Warrant.  Defendant now tells the court he wants to waive extradition.  
State of Indiana req extradition.
Defendant does not contest.
Colloquy conducted with def re: right to hearing.
BTC:  The court finds that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly, & intelligently waives extradition.
